Be aware that using this extended functionality requires a license for the corresponding pack. If you need to disable SQLT access to one of these packages, please execute one of the following commands: SQL> EXEC sqltxadmin.sqlt$a.disable_tuning_pack_access; or SQL> EXEC sqltxadmin.sqlt$a.disable_diagnostic_pack_access;

Observations

List of concerns identified by the health-check module. Please review. Some may require further attention.
# Type Priority Name Observation Details
1 TABLE COLUMN 85 T1.D An index should be created for a column referenced in a predicate. Also see MOS Note Diagnosing and Understanding Why a Query is Not Using an Index (Doc ID 67522.1). [+] Having this column included in an index allows the CBO to consider using such index to access or filter data more efficiently. Review predicate(s) where this column is used and consider including this column in an index (new or existing).
2 TABLE COLUMN 85 T2.D An index should be created for a column referenced in a predicate. Also see MOS Note Diagnosing and Understanding Why a Query is Not Using an Index (Doc ID 67522.1). [+] Having this column included in an index allows the CBO to consider using such index to access or filter data more efficiently. Review predicate(s) where this column is used and consider including this column in an index (new or existing).
3 PLAN 72 OPTIMIZER_ENV Check the applicability of having multiple CBO environmets set up for one SQL. AWR references 2 distinct CBO Environments. https://docs.oracle.com/database/121/REFRN/GUID-2B9340D7-4AA8-4894-94C0-D5990F67BE75.htm#REFRN30246 [+] Distinct CBO Environments may produce different Plans. Review Plan Performance History.
4 DBMS_STATS 66 DBA_AUTOTASK_CLIENT Ensure DBMS_STATS Automatic gathering sample size is sufficient. See MOS note How to: Manage CBO Statistics During an Upgrade from 10g or 9i into 11g/12c (Doc ID 465787.1) [+] Be aware that small sample sizes could produce poor quality histograms, which combined with bind sensitive predicates could render suboptimal plans. See MOS Doc ID 465787.1.
5 PLAN 48 SQL_PLAN_BASELINE Review the SQL Plan Baseline for applicability. SQL Plan History contains 2 Plan(s). 2 is/are reproduced and enabled and accepted (actual SQL Plan Baseline). [+] Review SQL Plan Baselines.
6 CBO PARAMETER 35 NON-DEFAULT Review the non-default CBO parameter mentioned to ensure it is needed. See https://docs.oracle.com/database/121/TGSQL/tgsql_influence.htm#TGSQL246 [+] Parameter value was specified in the parameter file. Review CBO Environment..
7 TABLE 35 PERFLAB.T1 Confirm statisitcs are correct. Check the effect of changing number of NDV on execution plans. Table contains 2 column(s) referenced in predicates with fluctuating number of distinct values. Also see Bug Bug 9885553 - DBMS_STATS produces incorrect column NDV distinct values statistics (Doc ID 9885553.8). [+] Review column statistics for this table and look for "Fluctuating NDV Count". There are column(s) referenced in predicates for which according to "Column Statistics Versions", the number of "Distinct Values" has changed in the near past. This could cause plan changes.
8 DBMS_STATS 33 SYSTEM STATISTICS Workload CBO System Statistics are not gathered. CBO is using default values. See MOS Note How to Collect and Display System Statistics (CPU and IO) for CBO use (Doc ID 149560.1) [+] Consider gathering workload system statistics using SYS.DBMS_STATS.GATHER_SYSTEM_STATS. See MOS Doc ID 465787.1.
9 TABLE COLUMN 29 T1.A Check the usefullness of creating a UNIQUE index on column T1.A. [+] Consider creating a UNIQUE index on this single column. It is used in predicates and the CBO could use it in some queries.
10 TABLE COLUMN 29 T2.A Check the usefullness of creating a UNIQUE index on column T2.A. [+] Consider creating a UNIQUE index on this single column. It is used in predicates and the CBO could use it in some queries.
11 SYSTEM PARAMETER 25 MODIFIED Review the modified system parameter mentioned to ensure it is needed. See https://docs.oracle.com/en/database/oracle/oracle-database/12.2/refrn/index.html [+] Parameter value was modified either in the parameter file or with an ALTER SYSTEM command. Review Modified System Parameters..
12 PLAN 23 PLAN_HASH_VALUE Ensure that you expect only one execution plan for this SQL. [+] Review Execution Plans.
13 PLAN CONTROL 22 PLAN_CONTROL Stored Outlines, SQL Profiles, SQL Patch and SQL Plan Baselines should be viewed as temporary measures. Determine the reason for these and collect statistics appropriately. [+] Review Execution Plans.
14 MAT_VIEW 9 REWRITE_ENABLED Check that all Materialized Views are applicable. There is/are 2 materialized view(s) with rewrite enabled. See MOS Note Master Note for Materialized View (MVIEW) (Doc ID 1353040.1). [+] A large number of materialized views could affect parsing time since CBO would have to evaluate each during a hard-parse.
15 TABLE COLUMN 9 T1.A Check to see if a NOT NULL constraint would be useful on T1.A. [+] Consider creating a NOT NULL constraint. CBO uses constraints to generate additional predicates that may help to improve selectivity computations referencing this column. Better computations may allow a better plan.
16 TABLE COLUMN 9 T1.D Check to see if a NOT NULL constraint would be useful on T1.D. [+] Consider creating a NOT NULL constraint. CBO uses constraints to generate additional predicates that may help to improve selectivity computations referencing this column. Better computations may allow a better plan.
17 TABLE COLUMN 9 T2.A Check to see if a NOT NULL constraint would be useful on T2.A. [+] Consider creating a NOT NULL constraint. CBO uses constraints to generate additional predicates that may help to improve selectivity computations referencing this column. Better computations may allow a better plan.
18 TABLE COLUMN 9 T2.D Check to see if a NOT NULL constraint would be useful on T2.D. [+] Consider creating a NOT NULL constraint. CBO uses constraints to generate additional predicates that may help to improve selectivity computations referencing this column. Better computations may allow a better plan.

DBMS_STATS Operations History

List restricted up to 300 rows as per tool parameter "r_rows_table_m".
SQL: [+] 
SELECT o.start_time,
       o.end_time,
       o.operation,
       o.target
  FROM sqltxplain.sqlt$_dba_optstat_operations o,
       sqltxadmin.sqlt$_dba_all_tables_v t
 WHERE o.statement_id = 39943
   AND UPPER(o.operation) LIKE '%TABLE%'
   AND o.statement_id = t.statement_id
   AND UPPER(o.target) LIKE '%'||UPPER(t.owner)||'%'
   AND UPPER(o.target) LIKE '%'||UPPER(t.table_name)||'%'
 UNION
SELECT o.start_time,
       o.end_time,
       o.operation,
       o.target
  FROM sqltxplain.sqlt$_dba_optstat_operations o,
       sqltxadmin.sqlt$_dba_all_tables_v t
 WHERE o.statement_id = 39943
   AND UPPER(o.operation) LIKE '%SCHEMA%'
   AND o.statement_id = t.statement_id
   AND UPPER(o.target) LIKE '%'||UPPER(t.owner)||'%'
 UNION
SELECT o.start_time,
       o.end_time,
       o.operation,
       o.target
  FROM sqlt$_dba_optstat_operations o,
       sqlt$_dba_indexes i
 WHERE o.statement_id = 39943
   AND UPPER(o.operation) LIKE '%INDEX%'
   AND o.statement_id = i.statement_id
   AND UPPER(o.target) LIKE '%'||UPPER(i.owner)||'%'
   AND UPPER(o.target) LIKE '%'||UPPER(i.index_name)||'%'
 UNION
SELECT o.start_time,
       o.end_time,
       o.operation,
       o.target
  FROM sqltxplain.sqlt$_dba_optstat_operations o
 WHERE o.statement_id = 39943
   AND UPPER(o.operation) NOT LIKE '%TABLE%'
   AND UPPER(o.operation) NOT LIKE '%SCHEMA%'
   AND UPPER(o.operation) NOT LIKE '%INDEX%'
 ORDER BY
       start_time DESC;

Modified System Parameters

[-] Historical values of modified initialization system-level parameters captured by AWR with no direct relation to the SQL being analyzed. Includes all instances. Excludes some parameters and all "__%" parameters
List restricted up to 300 rows as per tool parameter "r_rows_table_m".
SQL: [+] 
SELECT p.parameter_name,
       p.instance_number,
       p.end_interval_time,
       p.snap_id,
       p.isdefault,
       p.ismodified,
       p.value,
       p.oldest_value_on_awr
  FROM sqltxadmin.sqlt$_dba_hist_parameter_v p
 WHERE p.statement_id = 39943
 ORDER BY
       p.parameter_name,
       p.instance_number,
       p.end_interval_time DESC;

Active PX Servers

Statistics for active parallel-execution servers.
SQL: [+] 
SELECT e.inst_id,
       e.slave_name,
       p.status,
       e.sessions,
       e.idle_time_cur,
       e.busy_time_cur,
       e.cpu_secs_cur,
       e.msgs_sent_cur,
       e.msgs_rcvd_cur,
       e.idle_time_total,
       e.busy_time_total,
       e.cpu_secs_total,
       e.msgs_sent_total,
       e.msgs_rcvd_total,
       NVL(s.qcinst_id, s.inst_id) qcinst_id,
       s.qcsid
  FROM sqltxplain.sqlt$_gv$pq_slave e,
       sqltxplain.sqlt$_gv$px_process p,
       sqltxplain.sqlt$_gv$px_session s
 WHERE statement_id = 39943
   AND e.begin_end_flag = 'E'
   AND e.statement_id = p.statement_id
   AND e.inst_id = p.inst_id
   AND e.slave_name = p.server_name
   AND p.begin_end_flag = 'E'
   AND p.statement_id = s.statement_id(+)
   AND 'E' = s.begin_end_flag(+)
   AND p.inst_id = s.inst_id(+)
   AND p.sid = s.sid(+)
   AND p.serial# = s.serial#(+)
 ORDER BY
       e.inst_id,
       e.slave_name;

SELECT p.inst_id,
       p.server_name,
       p.status,
       p.pid,
       p.spid,
       p.sid,
       p.serial#,

       s.qcsid,
       NVL(s.qcserial#, s.serial#) qcserial#
  FROM sqltxplain.sqlt$_gv$px_process p,
       sqltxplain.sqlt$_gv$px_session s
 WHERE p.statement_id = 39943
   AND p.begin_end_flag = 'E'
   AND p.statement_id = s.statement_id(+)
   AND 'E' = s.begin_end_flag(+)
   AND p.inst_id = s.inst_id(+)

PX Sessions

Sessions running on parallel-execution servers.
SQL: [+] 
SELECT NVL(s.qcinst_id, s.inst_id) qcinst_id,
       s.qcsid,
       NVL(s.qcserial#, s.serial#) qcserial#,
       s.server_group,
       s.server_set,
       s.server#,
       s.degree,
       s.req_degree,
       s.inst_id,
       s.sid,
       s.serial#,
       p.server_name
  FROM sqltxplain.sqlt$_gv$px_session s,
       sqltxplain.sqlt$_gv$px_process p
 WHERE s.statement_id = 39943
   AND s.begin_end_flag = 'E'
   AND s.statement_id = p.statement_id(+)
   AND 'E' = p.begin_end_flag(+)
   AND s.inst_id = p.inst_id(+)
   AND s.sid = p.sid(+)
   AND s.serial# = p.serial#(+)
 ORDER BY
       NVL(s.qcinst_id, s.inst_id),
       s.qcsid,
       NVL(s.qcserial#, s.serial#),
       s.server_group NULLS FIRST,
       s.server_set NULLS FIRST,
       s.server# NULLS FIRST,
       s.inst_id,
       s.sid,
       s.serial#;

Table Statistics Versions

List of pending, current and historic CBO statistics, restricted up to 1000 rows as per tool parameter "r_rows_table_l".
SQL: [+] 
SELECT v.table_name,
       v.owner,
       v.version_type,
       v.save_time,
       v.last_analyzed,
       v.num_rows,
       v.sample_size,
       CASE WHEN v.num_rows > 0 THEN ROUND(v.sample_size * 100 / v.num_rows, 1) END percent,
       v.blocks,
       v.avg_row_len
  FROM sqltxadmin.sqlt$_dba_tab_stats_versions_v v
 WHERE v.statement_id = 39943
   AND v.object_type = 'TABLE'
 ORDER BY
       v.table_name,
       v.owner,
       DECODE(v.version_type,
       'PENDING', 1,
       'CURRENT', 2,
       'HISTORY', 3, 4),
       v.save_time DESC;

PERFLAB.T1 - Column Statistics Versions

Restricted list of pending, current and historic CBO statistics for columns in predicates, indexes or projections.
Further restricted up to 300 rows as per tool parameter "r_rows_table_m".
SQL: [+] 
SELECT c.in_predicates,
       c.in_indexes,
       c.in_projection,
       c.column_id,
       c.column_name,
       c.data_default,
       v.version_type,
       v.save_time,
       v.last_analyzed,
       v.num_nulls,
       v.sample_size,
       v.num_distinct,
       v.endpoints_count,
       v.low_value_cooked,
       v.high_value_cooked,
       v.avg_col_len,
       v.density
  FROM sqltxadmin.sqlt$_dba_col_stats_versions_v v,
       sqltxadmin.sqlt$_dba_all_table_cols_v c
 WHERE v.statement_id = 39943
   AND v.table_name = 'T1'
   AND v.owner = 'PERFLAB'
   AND v.object_type = 'TABLE'
   AND v.statement_id = c.statement_id
   AND v.column_name = c.column_name
   AND v.table_name = c.table_name
   AND v.owner = c.owner
   AND (c.in_predicates = 'TRUE' OR c.in_indexes = 'TRUE' OR c.in_projection = 'TRUE')
   --AND c.hidden_column = 'NO'
 ORDER BY
       c.in_predicates DESC,
       c.in_indexes DESC,
       c.in_projection DESC,
       c.column_id NULLS LAST,
       c.column_name,
       DECODE(v.version_type,
       'PENDING', 1,
       'CURRENT', 2,
       'HISTORY', 3, 4),
       v.save_time DESC;

b) Smallest bucket shows an estimated cardinality of 500000 rows, thus for equality predicates on values not in this histogram an estimated cardinality of 250000 rows would be considered.

1 FALSE T1I PERFLAB NORMAL NO N 500000 500000 100.0 2021-02-24/15:18:48 500000 2 25 1280 1280 1536 1148 1 1 3942 YES NO NO BEST 5092 0.108013 12582912
(1) CBO Statistics.
(2) It considers the blocks from all partitions (if the index is partitioned).
(3) This is the estimated size of the index if it were rebuilt, as computed by DBMS_SPACE.CREATE_INDEX_COST.
(4) Estimated leaf blocks with a 90% index efficiency. Only evaluated for non-partitioned normal indexes with more than 10000 leaf blocks.
(5) BEST:less than 126508. GOOD:between 126508 and 251006. POOR:between 251006 and 375503. WORST:greater than 375503.
(6) It assumes default CBO environment, including optimizer_index_cost_adj=100 and optimizer_index_caching=0 among others.
(7) Index Selectivity where Full Index Scan Cost meets Full Table Scan Cost. A value of 0.02 means that if selecting 2% of the rows or less, an index scan is cheaper than a FTS.
(8) Index Size if it were to be rebuilt, the estimation comes from EXPLAIN PLAN FOR of the CREATE INDEX command so it's dependent on good statistics.

PERFLAB.T1 - Index Statistics Versions

List of pending, current and historic CBO statistics, restricted up to 1000 rows as per tool parameter "r_rows_table_l".
SQL: [+] 
SELECT x.in_plan,
       v.index_name,
       v.owner,
       v.version_type,
       v.save_time,
       v.last_analyzed,
       v.num_rows,
       v.sample_size,
       CASE WHEN v.num_rows > 0 THEN ROUND(v.sample_size * 100 / v.num_rows, 1) END percent,
       v.distinct_keys,
       v.blevel,
       v.leaf_blocks,
       v.avg_leaf_blocks_per_key,
       v.avg_data_blocks_per_key,
       v.clustering_factor,
       v.global_stats,
       v.user_stats
  FROM sqltxadmin.sqlt$_dba_ind_stats_versions_v v,
       sqltxplain.sqlt$_dba_indexes x
 WHERE v.statement_id = 39943
   AND v.object_type = 'INDEX'
   AND v.table_name = 'T1'
   AND v.table_owner = 'PERFLAB'
   AND v.statement_id = x.statement_id
   AND v.owner = x.owner
   AND v.index_name = x.index_name
   AND v.table_owner = x.table_owner
   AND v.table_name = x.table_name
 ORDER BY
       x.in_plan DESC,
       v.index_name,
       v.owner,
       DECODE(v.version_type,
       'PENDING', 1,
       'CURRENT', 2,
       'HISTORY', 3, 4),
       v.save_time DESC;

PERFLAB.T1I - Column Statistics Versions

List of pending, current and historic CBO statistics, restricted up to 100 rows as per tool parameter "r_rows_table_s".
SQL: [+] 
SELECT ic.column_position,
       c.in_predicates,
       c.in_projection,
       c.column_id,
       c.column_name,
       c.data_default,
       v.version_type,
       v.save_time,
       v.last_analyzed,
       v.num_nulls,
       v.sample_size,
       v.num_distinct,
       v.endpoints_count,
       v.low_value_cooked,
       v.high_value_cooked,
       v.avg_col_len,
       v.density
  FROM sqltxplain.sqlt$_dba_ind_columns ic,
       sqltxadmin.sqlt$_dba_col_stats_versions_v v,
       sqltxadmin.sqlt$_dba_all_table_cols_v c
 WHERE ic.statement_id = 39943
   AND ic.index_name = 'T1I'
   AND ic.index_owner = 'PERFLAB'
   AND ic.statement_id = v.statement_id
   AND ic.table_name = v.table_name
   AND ic.table_owner = v.owner
   AND ic.column_name = v.column_name
   AND v.object_type = 'TABLE'
   AND ic.statement_id = c.statement_id
   AND ic.table_name = c.table_name
   AND ic.table_owner = c.owner
   AND ic.column_name = c.column_name
 ORDER BY
       ic.column_position,
       DECODE(v.version_type,
       'PENDING', 1,
       'CURRENT', 2,
       'HISTORY', 3, 4),
       v.save_time DESC;

PERFLAB.T2 - Index Statistics

# In Plan Index Name Owner Index Type Part Temp Num Rows1 Sample Size1 Perc Last Analyzed1 Distinct Keys1 Blevel1 Segment Extents Segment Blocks Total Segment Blocks2 DBMS_SPACE Allocated Blocks3 Leaf Blocks1 Leaf Estimate Target Size4 Avg Leaf Blocks per Key1 Avg Data Blocks per Key1 Clustering Factor1 Global Stats1 User Stats1 Stat Type Locked Stale Stats Avg Cached Blocks Avg Cache Hit Ratio Clustering Factor Quality5 Full Index Scan Cost6 Max Index Selectivity7 Estimated Size If Rebuilt8
1 TRUE T2I PERFLAB NORMAL NO N 500000 500000 100.0 2021-02-24/15:18:49 500000 2 25 1280 1280 1536 1148 1 1 3942 YES NO NO BEST 5092 0.108013 12582912
(1) CBO Statistics.
(2) It considers the blocks from all partitions (if the index is partitioned).
(3) This is the estimated size of the index if it were rebuilt, as computed by DBMS_SPACE.CREATE_INDEX_COST.
(4) Estimated leaf blocks with a 90% index efficiency. Only evaluated for non-partitioned normal indexes with more than 10000 leaf blocks.
(5) BEST:less than 126508. GOOD:between 126508 and 251006. POOR:between 251006 and 375503. WORST:greater than 375503.
(6) It assumes default CBO environment, including optimizer_index_cost_adj=100 and optimizer_index_caching=0 among others.
(7) Index Selectivity where Full Index Scan Cost meets Full Table Scan Cost. A value of 0.02 means that if selecting 2% of the rows or less, an index scan is cheaper than a FTS.
(8) Index Size if it were to be rebuilt, the estimation comes from EXPLAIN PLAN FOR of the CREATE INDEX command so it's dependent on good statistics.

PERFLAB.T2 - Index Statistics Versions

List of pending, current and historic CBO statistics, restricted up to 1000 rows as per tool parameter "r_rows_table_l".
SQL: [+] 
SELECT x.in_plan,
       v.index_name,
       v.owner,
       v.version_type,
       v.save_time,
       v.last_analyzed,
       v.num_rows,
       v.sample_size,
       CASE WHEN v.num_rows > 0 THEN ROUND(v.sample_size * 100 / v.num_rows, 1) END percent,
       v.distinct_keys,
       v.blevel,
       v.leaf_blocks,
       v.avg_leaf_blocks_per_key,
       v.avg_data_blocks_per_key,
       v.clustering_factor,
       v.global_stats,
       v.user_stats
  FROM sqltxadmin.sqlt$_dba_ind_stats_versions_v v,
       sqltxplain.sqlt$_dba_indexes x
 WHERE v.statement_id = 39943
   AND v.object_type = 'INDEX'
   AND v.table_name = 'T2'
   AND v.table_owner = 'PERFLAB'
   AND v.statement_id = x.statement_id
   AND v.owner = x.owner
   AND v.index_name = x.index_name
   AND v.table_owner = x.table_owner
   AND v.table_name = x.table_name
 ORDER BY
       x.in_plan DESC,
       v.index_name,
       v.owner,
       DECODE(v.version_type,
       'PENDING', 1,
       'CURRENT', 2,
       'HISTORY', 3, 4),
       v.save_time DESC;

PERFLAB.T2I - Column Statistics Versions

List of pending, current and historic CBO statistics, restricted up to 100 rows as per tool parameter "r_rows_table_s".
SQL: [+] 
SELECT ic.column_position,
       c.in_predicates,
       c.in_projection,
       c.column_id,
       c.column_name,
       c.data_default,
       v.version_type,
       v.save_time,
       v.last_analyzed,
       v.num_nulls,
       v.sample_size,
       v.num_distinct,

       v.low_value_cooked,
       v.high_value_cooked,
       v.avg_col_len,
       v.density
  FROM sqltxplain.sqlt$_dba_ind_columns ic,
       sqltxadmin.sqlt$_dba_col_stats_versions_v v,
       sqltxadmin.sqlt$_dba_all_table_cols_v c
 WHERE ic.statement_id = 39943
   AND ic.index_name = 'T2I'
   AND ic.index_owner = 'PERFLAB'
   AND ic.statement_id = v.statement_id
   AND ic.table_name = v.table_name
   AND ic.table_owner = v.owner
   AND ic.column_name = v.column_name
   AND v.object_type = 'TABLE'
   AND ic.statement_id = c.statement_id
   AND ic.table_name = c.table_name
   AND ic.table_owner = c.owner
   AND ic.column_name = c.column_name
 ORDER BY
       ic.column_position,
       DECODE(v.version_type,
       'PENDING', 1,
       'CURRENT', 2,
       'HISTORY', 3, 4),
       v.save_time DESC;

Objects

Restricted list of objects related to the SQL being analyzed. Partitions and Subpartitions are excluded.
Further restricted up to 1000 rows as per tool parameter "r_rows_table_l".
SQL: [+] 
SELECT o.object_type,
       o.object_name,
       o.owner,
       o.object_id,
       o.data_object_id,
       o.created,
       o.last_ddl_time,
       o.timestamp,
       o.status,
       o.temporary,
       o.generated,
       o.secondary,
       o.namespace,
       o.edition_name,
       o.metadata_error
  FROM sqltxplain.sqlt$_dba_objects o
 WHERE o.statement_id = 39943
   AND o.object_type NOT LIKE '%PARTITION'
 ORDER BY
       o.object_type,
       o.object_name,
       o.subobject_name;
